  "status": "Draft",
  "summary": "A puppet is a contract that, when called, acts like an empty account. It doesn't do anything and it has no API, except when it is called by the address that deployed it. In that case, it delegates the call to the address passed to it in calldata. This gives the deployer the ability to execute any logic they want in the context of the puppet.",
  "title": "Puppet Proxy Contract"
}